title: AHS 1984 Episode 9 Review & Synopsis
author: MaryGirl Moody
comment: I'm so glad that after so much shit, you finally got to post your original Episode 9 review. It was well worth the wait! ❤️
1984 was EPIC! Everything you said... right on the head, nailed it. Loved this season.
The poor Duke family. They lost both their son and their daughter. They’re the real victims in this.

I’m so glad we didn’t have to wait until January to get the video you wanted to post Mary! Also I would like to say I loved this season but only the last three episodes. It felt very slow but got good towards the end of the season. Also I loved the ending with Brook and Donna being the final girls in the end! Both living happy and successful lives. This is the first season of AHS to have an ending that is satisfying.
I love that there were hints to other seasons
